1
00:01:05,765 --> 00:01:08,666
She is calling you. There's very
little time, please hurry.

2
00:02:03,823 --> 00:02:06,724
As per Ms. Bhavna's will...

3
00:02:06,893 --> 00:02:10,522
...her son, Rahul's inheritance
has been entrusted to you.

4
00:02:15,835 --> 00:02:17,928
Are you her relative?

5
00:02:19,839 --> 00:02:21,238
No.

6
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:24,275
Did you know her since long?

7
00:02:24,444 --> 00:02:26,776
Since the time she was in school.

8
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:34,317
The inheritance she's left for
her son has been put in a Trust.

9
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:36,819
Once all the documents are ready,
they will be sent to you.

10
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:44,228
Where will you
take the child now?

11
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:50,334
Does yourfamily live there...

12
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:52,835
No. l live alone.

13
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:57,874
Will you look after a small child
in this old age?

14
00:02:58,978 --> 00:03:00,309
l mean...

15
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,338
...doesn't he have a father?

16
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:14,354
Anyway, once the documents are
ready, we will send them to you.

17
00:05:37,036 --> 00:05:39,937
Take him away!
...Mummy! Take him away!

18
00:05:52,618 --> 00:05:56,019
-What's the matter?
- Sister, take the dog away!

19
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:01,889
-Who brought it?
- Papa did.

20
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:04,894
-You're scared of a tiny dog?!
- No way! l'm not scared.

21
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:06,895
You aren't, right? Now watch!

22
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,403
No! l'll tell mummy!

23
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:15,903
You aren't scared, right? Look!

24
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:22,947
This point here...
Please let there be light.

25
00:06:23,116 --> 00:06:25,346
You had to provide ramps
from here to this point.

26
00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:29,987
And what are
these proportions! Are you...

27
00:06:36,095 --> 00:06:37,995
Speak softly, my dear.
What's the matter?

28
00:06:39,098 --> 00:06:40,998
What did the dog do?

29
00:06:42,101 --> 00:06:45,502
l'll be home soon.
ls your mummy there?

30
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:48,039
No? ...Thank God!

31
00:06:48,207 --> 00:06:50,038
And listen! lf she
returns soon, don't tell her.

32
00:06:50,209 --> 00:06:53,542
l'll be there before she does.
...Yes, my dear!

33
00:06:54,147 --> 00:06:56,047
My wife loves dogs, sir.

34
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,840
My wife hates them.

35
00:07:07,059 --> 00:07:09,960
You get dead tired, going out
in this city in the traffic!

36
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:11,960
l left at 4 O'clock!

37
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:16,967
Here are your colour pencils.
Don't lose them again.

38
00:07:19,071 --> 00:07:22,006
Where has the flower vase gone
from here? Who has removed it?

39
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:23,574
Abdul, get me some water.

40
00:07:32,151 --> 00:07:34,551
-Where has the flower vase gone?
- l don't know.

41
00:07:35,154 --> 00:07:37,554
Nobody in this house
ever knows anything!

42
00:07:38,357 --> 00:07:39,824
Here are your pencils.

43
00:07:45,164 --> 00:07:48,565
Hey! Who's kept a cactus
in place of the photo frame?

44
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:55,072
She's always missing!
She's never at home!

45
00:07:58,711 --> 00:08:00,542
Why are all of you
sitting so quietly?

46
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:07,519
Hear, hear!
Can't we sit quietly at home?

47
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:12,022
lndeed! l know what it means
when all of you sit quietly!

48
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,024
Papa, mummy is going to
the bathroom to wash herface.

49
00:08:18,197 --> 00:08:19,357
Oh! We'll be damned!

50
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:23,031
lndu... uh... are you
going to the bathroom?

51
00:08:25,137 --> 00:08:26,035
What!

52
00:08:26,205 --> 00:08:28,036
Are you going to wash yourface?

53
00:08:28,574 --> 00:08:30,405
-Why?
- For no reason.

54
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:34,078
l've heard that washing the face
too much spoils the skin.

55
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:36,078
Where did you hearthat?

56
00:08:36,249 --> 00:08:38,080
Well... Mini was saying so.

57
00:08:38,284 --> 00:08:40,684
No, papa! Sister said so.

58
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:44,118
No! Even l didn't say so! ...
Mummy, l'd heard it on the radio.

59
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:47,124
-Yes! We'd heard it on the radio.
-What's wrong with all of you?!

60
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:53,130
We are doomed now!

61
00:08:53,299 --> 00:08:54,197
Yes.

62
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:07,044
Take this dog away!
Who brought it here?!

63
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:10,046
l said, take the dog away!

64
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:13,084
Who brought it here?!

65
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:16,654
l asked, who brought it here?!

66
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:22,592
Let's go.

67
00:09:23,195 --> 00:09:25,095
l knew it!

68
00:09:25,264 --> 00:09:27,357
- Please let the dog stay here.
- Quiet!

69
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:32,102
The dog broke a photo frame,
a flower vase and tore a curtain!

70
00:09:32,271 --> 00:09:34,671
These were the disasters
struck on the very first day!

71
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:38,139
lt'll destroy the whole house in
no time! Who'll take care of it?

72
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:40,142
We'll put a leash around it.

73
00:09:40,313 --> 00:09:43,339
There's no need!
Who asked you to get it?!

74
00:09:44,283 --> 00:09:48,686
Bela is not yet here!
She is always missing!

75
00:09:50,489 --> 00:09:53,185
l'm warning you,
l will not keep the dog!

76
00:09:55,294 --> 00:09:57,194
How often have l said,
throw away those glasses!

77
00:09:58,297 --> 00:09:59,628
Hey! How will l read then!

78
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:02,199
-You look just like a peon!
- So what?

79
00:10:07,306 --> 00:10:09,240
How's your backache?

80
00:10:10,343 --> 00:10:14,712
lt's okay now but l had to
stand in the site for 2-3 hours.

81
00:10:14,914 --> 00:10:16,245
l'll massage it.

82
00:10:18,384 --> 00:10:20,784
Why do you have to work so much?

83
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:25,287
Come off it! l work for
you and your children.

84
00:10:25,891 --> 00:10:29,292
Stop it! ...
You are fond of working!

85
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,293
We have everything.

86
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:33,295
Everything is what we don't have.

87
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,799
What do we lack?

88
00:10:36,402 --> 00:10:38,302
A diamond necklace.

89
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:40,302
Well, who wants one!

90
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:45,843
Oh really! Then, why were you
lustily eyeing Kanta's necklace?

91
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:49,846
Nonsense! l was looking at it
because it was so ugly!

92
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:50,914
l see.

93
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:55,887
Forget the necklace but you'd
surely want a husband like hers?

94
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:59,886
Get me the most precious gem, yet
l wouldn't want a man like Suri.

95
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:01,822
What kind of
a husband do you want?

96
00:11:05,364 --> 00:11:07,264
l have one.

97
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:12,262
Yes, you do. But do sing praises
about him sometimes!

98
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:18,809
Shall l say something?

99
00:11:20,413 --> 00:11:22,313
Let's keep the puppy at home?

100
00:11:22,481 --> 00:11:24,312
You sly monkey!

101
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:29,512
Yuck! l'm not going to
drink this! There's cream in it!

102
00:11:29,955 --> 00:11:32,355
Nothing doing! Drink the milk!

103
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,924
Keep your hand down!

104
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:36,357
How will l drink my coffee then?!

105
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:37,791
Use the other hand.

106
00:11:37,963 --> 00:11:39,794
Keep papa's name as puppy.

107
00:11:39,965 --> 00:11:41,956
Stupid! Keep the puppy's
name as papa!

108
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:44,969
Stop fighting
early in the morning!

109
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,371
-Allow me to take the coffee.
- No!

110
00:11:47,573 --> 00:11:49,905
The puppy drinks milk,
not coffee.

111
00:11:50,076 --> 00:11:53,409
l'm not talking about
the puppy... but about papa.

112
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,413
Shall we name him also Mini?

113
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,415
ls that a name!

114
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:02,316
Naming him Mini
will create a problem.

115
00:12:02,488 --> 00:12:04,319
lf we call the puppy,
you'll come running...

116
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,822
...and if we call you,
it will come running!

117
00:12:07,426 --> 00:12:09,826
When there will be no dog,
what's the use of finding a name?

118
00:12:12,631 --> 00:12:14,826
Have you had your vitamins?

119
00:12:15,434 --> 00:12:16,833
- Have you?
-Yes, papa.

120
00:12:17,002 --> 00:12:19,334
- l'm asking you also.
-Yes, even l've had it.

121
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:22,931
Papa, you lie?

122
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:37,921
Don't forget we have to go to
Mr. Suri's party in the evening.

123
00:12:39,525 --> 00:12:42,926
There's a tank
filled with hot water.

124
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:48,931
ln it, your host, his wife
and you are almost naked!

125
00:12:50,536 --> 00:12:54,438
The pressure of the hot water
massages your body!

126
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,835
And you get tickled all over.

127
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:02,346
-Adjust yourtie properly!
-What's wrong with it?

128
00:13:02,515 --> 00:13:03,846
-You've come for a party.
- lt's okay.

129
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:05,540
Hey, you Late Kate!

130
00:13:10,089 --> 00:13:11,989
- Suri, how are you?
-Absolutely fine.

131
00:13:12,158 --> 00:13:14,888
Mr. Suri, DK will not
drink too much today.

132
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:18,029
- The question does not arise!
- lndeed! He gets high with 2 pegs!

133
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:22,896
And listen... please don't
recite couplets either!

134
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:24,399
l can't promise that.

135
00:13:25,004 --> 00:13:27,404
All right! But do everything
within your limits, DK!

136
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,942
Let's have a very large peg.

137
00:13:32,545 --> 00:13:34,877
l had no idea that
there'd be so many people.

138
00:13:35,047 --> 00:13:36,947
Bring a glass of
champagne for him.

139
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:38,515
We'll have a large peg later.

140
00:13:50,596 --> 00:13:52,086
Listen to what l say!

141
00:13:55,601 --> 00:14:00,868
Son, he makes films. Deliver
the dialogues from Sholay'.

142
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,408
''How many men were there?''
''Two, sir.''

143
00:14:04,577 --> 00:14:07,410
''And you were three.
Yet, you returned empty-handed!''

144
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,979
He's good, isn't he?

145
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,450
You were to phone me
day before yesterday!

146
00:14:13,619 --> 00:14:15,450
l was busy, l had to go out.

147
00:14:15,621 --> 00:14:17,953
You are always busy
with your work!

148
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:20,455
You were going to
quit smoking, weren't you?

149
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:22,958
- From tomorrow.
- Tomorrow indeed!

150
00:14:32,571 --> 00:14:35,972
Hadn't you worn the
same one for Sheetal's party?

151
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:37,506
They are very beautiful.

152
00:14:37,676 --> 00:14:39,507
- Hasn't Ratna come?
- l did call her.

153
00:14:39,678 --> 00:14:42,010
But you know her condition.

154
00:14:42,181 --> 00:14:45,514
ldiot! She keeps crying, and that
too away from her husband's eyes.

155
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,515
She doesn't protest by
eitherfighting or crying!

156
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,709
Meaning?

157
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:05,936
Remember, DK, in those days,
your athleticism...

158
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:08,973
And my naughtiness...

159
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:11,474
How many girls went crazy!

160
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,978
Any letters from the Major?

161
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,477
lt's a thing of the past.
Forget it!

162
00:15:19,618 --> 00:15:21,085
Have you forgotten?

163
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:25,517
Why do you worry?
Don't l look fine?

164
00:15:27,293 --> 00:15:32,026
''Raise not your hands
and arch backwards''

165
00:15:32,197 --> 00:15:37,032
''Take a look at your bosom''

166
00:15:37,202 --> 00:15:39,102
''As slowly
slides down your veil''

167
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,738
Wow! What a couplet!

168
00:15:43,175 --> 00:15:46,542
Remember, there was a song...

169
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:54,085
''O' lovely maiden, walk not
with your nose in the air''

170
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:57,621
Should we sing?

171
00:15:58,223 --> 00:15:59,622
Will you sing?

172
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:09,999
l have a bad throat.
Why don't you begin?

173
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:12,501
- Putting up your price, huh?
- No way!

174
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,541
You start, l'll join you.

175
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:23,046
What are you doing!

176
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:37,954
- How is Ratna now?
- l don't know.

177
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:00,012
Lie straight.

178
00:22:02,521 --> 00:22:03,920
No, Ratna, don't cry.

179
00:22:13,031 --> 00:22:16,933
Was your problem solved by
swallowing sleeping pills? ...No!

180
00:22:17,102 --> 00:22:19,935
You should have given them
to your husband instead!

181
00:22:20,105 --> 00:22:22,938
Orto his mistress!

182
00:22:23,141 --> 00:22:24,972
What will you gain by dying?!

183
00:22:25,143 --> 00:22:28,601
Quiet, Chanda! ls this
the time to scold her?!

184
00:22:36,321 --> 00:22:37,982
You're here?

185
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:40,523
What have you come to take now?!

186
00:22:43,128 --> 00:22:45,562
You've put Ratna in this state!
What more do you want to do?!

187
00:22:45,731 --> 00:22:47,631
- Please be quiet, Chanda.
-Why should l?!

188
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:49,529
Somebody has to speak!

189
00:22:49,701 --> 00:22:52,534
Should everyone be quiet like her
and let this man do as he please?

190
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:54,535
Let's go... We'll leave now.

191
00:23:00,412 --> 00:23:02,437
Think and talk!

192
00:23:02,614 --> 00:23:05,947
lf you were in her shoes,
would you think and talk?!

193
00:23:10,088 --> 00:23:12,989
Sleeping pills
do not solve problems.

194
00:23:14,092 --> 00:23:16,492
But her husband is also crazy.

195
00:23:16,661 --> 00:23:18,993
How can he change,
even after having children?

196
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:22,993
lf you can't bearthe
responsibility, why get married?

197
00:23:24,603 --> 00:23:28,505
Mummy, if l were not born,
what would have happened?

198
00:23:30,142 --> 00:23:33,043
Then there would have been
a baby boy in your place!

199
00:23:33,211 --> 00:23:34,200
My brother.

200
00:23:34,646 --> 00:23:38,013
- Not yours but mine!
- He'd have been my brothertoo.

201
00:23:38,216 --> 00:23:40,684
How would he, stupid!
You wouldn't be born!

202
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:45,520
Don't! Does one talk this way
with an elder sister?

203
00:23:45,690 --> 00:23:47,590
Does one speak this way
with a younger sister?

204
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:49,590
l'll beat you!
You call me stupid!

205
00:23:54,199 --> 00:23:55,598
Hey, you'll fall!

206
00:23:57,202 --> 00:23:59,102
That's enough now!

207
00:24:01,072 --> 00:24:04,007
Go to your room.

208
00:24:11,116 --> 00:24:13,550
lndu, suppose you
had a baby boy, then?

209
00:24:15,153 --> 00:24:16,552
l have one.

210
00:24:17,155 --> 00:24:20,056
Where is he?
Have you hidden him?

211
00:24:21,159 --> 00:24:24,560
Here he is!
lsn't he enough for me?

212
00:24:30,168 --> 00:24:31,328
Why?

213
00:24:33,672 --> 00:24:37,073
You have one, l don't.

214
00:24:38,210 --> 00:24:44,080
You don't even tell me whether
l've received a reply or not.

215
00:24:44,282 --> 00:24:47,115
lf there was, then l'd have
come to you immediately.

216
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,651
Why do you worry when l'm around?

217
00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:53,656
Worried, l certainly am.

218
00:24:54,259 --> 00:24:57,660
About this boy.
After all, l'm getting older.

219
00:24:57,829 --> 00:25:01,026
Here, send him
a telegram this time.

220
00:25:02,133 --> 00:25:04,533
Get yourself treated properly.

221
00:25:04,703 --> 00:25:07,536
- ls there a cure for old age?
-Why do you talk like this...

222
00:25:07,739 --> 00:25:10,572
Go and send
a telegram immediately.

223
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:27,123
- There's a telegram.
- From whom?

224
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:33,120
From Nainital?

225
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:35,630
He's asked you to come at once,
as there's some important work.

226
00:25:38,737 --> 00:25:41,672
-Who is he?
- The headmaster of my old school.

227
00:25:45,277 --> 00:25:47,677
-Anything important?
- l don't know.

228
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:49,177
He has never before...

229
00:25:50,282 --> 00:25:52,682
- l haven't met him since years.
- Then?

230
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:55,718
l'll phone him from office.

231
00:26:12,704 --> 00:26:14,103
Gupta, check this.

232
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:17,139
Bring it in.

233
00:26:27,285 --> 00:26:28,684
Mr. Dhawan is waiting foryou.

234
00:26:28,853 --> 00:26:30,684
- ls the new client here?
-Yes.

235
00:26:30,855 --> 00:26:32,686
-What's his name?
- Mr. Bansal.

236
00:26:34,292 --> 00:26:37,784
Listen... get me a trunk call
to Nainital. This is the number.

237
00:26:47,806 --> 00:26:49,740
And this is the embassy.

238
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:53,742
And yes! This is Neelkamal
Building, of which you mentioned.

239
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:57,247
These are its schematic designs.

240
00:26:59,384 --> 00:27:02,148
Come, DK. We were waiting
foryou... This is Mr. Bansal.

241
00:27:04,255 --> 00:27:05,654
Please sit, DK.

242
00:27:09,894 --> 00:27:14,661
He wants to build a complex -
Bansal Bhavan... is that the name?

243
00:27:15,266 --> 00:27:17,666
He wants us
to give him a proposal.

244
00:27:18,269 --> 00:27:20,669
You will be giving
the first presentation.

245
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:24,707
l was showing him the schematic
designs of Neelkamal Building.

246
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:27,210
-You explain to him.
- Sure.

247
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:32,214
No. Mr. Gurudayal has retired.

248
00:27:32,384 --> 00:27:35,251
- Please give me his phone number.
- He doesn't have a phone.

249
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:37,217
Who's speaking?

250
00:27:37,355 --> 00:27:40,256
DK from Delhi. l've received
a telegram from Mr. Gurudayal.

251
00:27:40,425 --> 00:27:43,258
-Are you DK Malhotra?
-Yes. Who are you?

252
00:27:43,428 --> 00:27:45,259
My name is Tiwari.

253
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:49,766
l had sent you the telegram.
The master had sent a lettertoo.

254
00:27:49,934 --> 00:27:51,765
- l haven't received the letter.
-You haven't?

255
00:27:51,936 --> 00:27:55,269
But l did get his telegram.
Mr. Tiwari, what work did he have?

256
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:56,770
lt's something very personal...

257
00:27:58,076 --> 00:28:01,807
-What work did he have?
-Are you really DK Malhotra?

258
00:28:02,781 --> 00:28:06,148
Yes, l am DK speaking!
What work did he have?

259
00:28:06,384 --> 00:28:08,716
He's asked you to come
to Nainital. Your son...

260
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:13,791
What did the master say?

261
00:28:14,325 --> 00:28:16,816
He says he has
very little time, and...

262
00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:19,225
All right! But what
work does he have with me?

263
00:28:19,397 --> 00:28:22,423
He wants you to take away
your son from here.

264
00:28:23,334 --> 00:28:24,426
Son!

265
00:28:25,336 --> 00:28:26,735
Whose son?

266
00:28:28,339 --> 00:28:31,274
l have no son.
What are you talking about?!

267
00:28:40,752 --> 00:28:42,777
Hello, Mr. Tiwari?!

268
00:28:42,987 --> 00:28:47,321
What is the matter? Do you know
what else the master has said?

269
00:28:47,492 --> 00:28:49,551
Yes. A small boy
lives in his house.

270
00:28:49,928 --> 00:28:52,328
Since the time his mother
left him with the master...

271
00:28:52,497 --> 00:28:54,829
Hello! Who's left him?

272
00:28:54,999 --> 00:28:56,830
His mother - Bhavna.

273
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,239
l see.

274
00:29:05,744 --> 00:29:07,211
Yes, Mr. Tiwari? ...

275
00:29:28,399 --> 00:29:30,799
-Worked up about something?
- No.

276
00:29:34,405 --> 00:29:36,339
Did you phone Nainital?

277
00:29:36,508 --> 00:29:41,343
Yes. The master was not there but
l spoke to a man named Mr. Tiwari.

278
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:42,912
lndu, he said...

279
00:29:48,486 --> 00:29:49,885
What did he say?

280
00:29:50,488 --> 00:29:53,389
He said that
the master was unwell...

281
00:29:53,992 --> 00:29:56,392
The line was bad,
l couldn't hear properly.

282
00:29:56,561 --> 00:30:00,395
But he did say that
the master was unwell.

283
00:30:00,565 --> 00:30:02,396
Send him some money
for his treatment.

284
00:30:02,567 --> 00:30:05,400
- lndu, that's not all.
- Then what is it?

285
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:10,798
l have some problem.

286
00:30:14,546 --> 00:30:18,414
What is that problem
of yours which isn't mine?

287
00:30:24,589 --> 00:30:26,056
What is it?

288
00:30:27,592 --> 00:30:28,991
Nothing.

289
00:30:30,595 --> 00:30:32,495
lt's an office problem.

290
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:52,048
- lt's me.
-Yes, lndu?

291
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:54,047
There's a letterfrom Nainital.
Shall l read it?

292
00:30:54,252 --> 00:30:57,585
- Have you read it?
- No. l've not even opened it.

293
00:30:57,755 --> 00:30:59,586
- Shall l open it?
- No, don't.

294
00:31:00,191 --> 00:31:03,456
l'll come home in the evening
and read it. Okay?

295
00:31:04,562 --> 00:31:09,465
Or l'll send the office peon.
Give it to him.

296
00:31:22,113 --> 00:31:23,512
Anita, cancel all appointments.

297
00:31:42,166 --> 00:31:47,570
''DK, she never wanted you
to know about this child.''

298
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:51,106
''When l learnt about it
afterthe child was born...

299
00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:54,109
...Bhavna had said
just one thing.''

300
00:31:54,279 --> 00:31:59,615
''Do not tell DK, since he has
his own life... his own family.'''

301
00:32:06,124 --> 00:32:09,025
''That child
neither laughs nor cries.''

302
00:32:09,193 --> 00:32:12,526
''He keeps staring out
of the window all day long.''

303
00:32:12,697 --> 00:32:14,597
''Waiting for, l wonder, whom.''

304
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:19,032
''lt appears as if his childhood
is vanishing at such a young age.''

305
00:32:19,203 --> 00:32:22,036
''l cannot give him anything
in my old age.''

306
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:28,076
''He needs a mother,
a father... a family, DK.''

307
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:34,378
''He asks me questions whose
answers l can't give, you can.''

308
00:32:40,925 --> 00:32:44,122
''Son, l won't live
very long now.''

309
00:32:44,295 --> 00:32:48,129
''Before l die, l want
to send your son to you.''

310
00:33:06,884 --> 00:33:08,943
Mummy, shout at her!

311
00:33:09,687 --> 00:33:11,086
Stupid, shut it!

312
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:14,089
You stupid! They are
showing Chintu's songs!

313
00:33:15,693 --> 00:33:18,093
- Mummy, ask herto shut it!
- Concentrate here!

314
00:33:18,696 --> 00:33:20,254
What to do about this?

315
00:33:20,698 --> 00:33:23,599
- Make blocks of these sums.
- How do you do that?

316
00:33:23,768 --> 00:33:26,100
That's what l don't know,
so l'm asking you.

317
00:33:26,270 --> 00:33:28,101
O God! Your New Math is tough!

318
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:30,105
Mini, stop your chorus!

319
00:33:30,308 --> 00:33:32,640
They are showing Chintu's songs.

320
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:34,641
ls Chintu your uncle?!

321
00:33:36,748 --> 00:33:38,079
Shut it!

322
00:33:38,249 --> 00:33:40,183
Mummy, please! They're showing
Uncle Chintu's songs!

323
00:33:40,351 --> 00:33:41,648
lt's disturbing.

324
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:44,185
Forget that.
Mummy, first tell me...

325
00:33:44,789 --> 00:33:46,188
Stop it, Mini!

326
00:33:46,357 --> 00:33:49,690
Mummy, l stand first in all the
other subjects except Maths...

327
00:33:52,797 --> 00:33:54,196
Papa, you're here!

328
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:57,698
Papa, they were showing Uncle
Chintu's songs but mummy shut it!

329
00:33:57,869 --> 00:33:59,700
Who's Uncle Chintu?

330
00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:02,567
Damn! How many times have l
told you about Uncle Chintu!

331
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:06,608
Quiet! ...Papa, ljust
cannot solve this sum.

332
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:08,109
Ask mummy.

333
00:34:08,279 --> 00:34:11,612
She doesn't know.
You explain, papa.

334
00:34:12,750 --> 00:34:16,151
No way! Thank God, you've come.
You handle them!

335
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:19,655
-Will you have tea?
-Yes. - Papa, please explain!

336
00:34:19,824 --> 00:34:22,657
-Add little sugar.
- Papa, solve the sum first.

337
00:34:22,827 --> 00:34:23,657
Fine.

338
00:34:26,964 --> 00:34:29,159
Doing Winky's homework
is beyond me.

339
00:34:29,767 --> 00:34:31,667
ln any case, l was weak in Math.

340
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,669
And l don't know about these new
blocks to be made in New Math.

341
00:34:34,839 --> 00:34:36,670
From now on, you manage her.

342
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:42,177
lf that fatso stands first in
class, Winky will not forgive me!

343
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:44,213
Get up!

344
00:34:45,817 --> 00:34:47,751
Won't you change your clothes?

345
00:34:51,856 --> 00:34:53,756
l want to tell you something.

346
00:34:55,126 --> 00:34:56,354
Go ahead.

347
00:34:58,863 --> 00:35:00,831
You won't like it.

348
00:35:03,734 --> 00:35:04,826
What's it?

349
00:35:05,736 --> 00:35:08,830
Let it be.
l'll tell you some othertime.

350
00:35:10,775 --> 00:35:12,174
lt's nothing.

351
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:14,675
Please, DK! Don't say this.

352
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:24,219
What is it?

353
00:35:30,828 --> 00:35:32,728
There was another girl in my life.

354
00:35:38,336 --> 00:35:41,737
- Don't joke about such matters.
- l am not joking, lndu.

355
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:51,781
l am not joking.

356
00:35:58,422 --> 00:36:01,687
When l... had gone... there...

357
00:36:02,793 --> 00:36:05,193
-Where?
- To Nainital.

358
00:36:05,796 --> 00:36:08,697
Forthe school's
Old Boys' function...

359
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,199
At that time...

360
00:36:12,003 --> 00:36:14,699
...Winky was going to be born.

361
00:36:15,072 --> 00:36:15,970
Yes.

362
00:36:18,843 --> 00:36:21,744
l'd met herthere.

363
00:36:23,848 --> 00:36:25,076
Who?

364
00:36:25,883 --> 00:36:28,943
Bhavna... that girl.

365
00:36:33,891 --> 00:36:34,789
l...

366
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:39,795
l don't know...
how l couldn't control myself.

367
00:36:40,898 --> 00:36:45,801
Perhaps because l was alone,
and... so was she.

368
00:36:46,904 --> 00:36:49,304
l went to her house once and...

369
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:53,342
...at her insistence,
l stayed back at night.

370
00:36:53,945 --> 00:36:57,813
l shouldn't have stayed back...
l shouldn't have stayed but...

371
00:37:07,358 --> 00:37:10,259
l never ever saw her
afterthat... l swear!

372
00:37:10,861 --> 00:37:14,262
And even then, l shared
nothing special with her.

373
00:37:14,865 --> 00:37:16,765
You shared nothing special?!

374
00:37:20,871 --> 00:37:23,271
What can be more special
than this, DK?

375
00:37:29,113 --> 00:37:32,605
So, what does she want now?

376
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:35,145
Nothing. She's dead.

377
00:37:39,957 --> 00:37:41,049
Then?

378
00:37:46,464 --> 00:37:48,864
She has a son from me.

379
00:37:51,969 --> 00:37:55,063
No! Don't say that!

380
00:37:56,007 --> 00:37:59,875
What's happening!
Please don't say that!

381
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:05,280
l'm very scared.

382
00:38:17,928 --> 00:38:20,829
Winky dear, go and sleep.

383
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:33,334
You said you've been busy.
So what brings you here today?

384
00:39:33,504 --> 00:39:35,404
l want to talk to you...
There's a big problem.

385
00:39:35,606 --> 00:39:41,442
With Bansal? lf you want, l'll
phone him now and fix matters.

386
00:39:42,046 --> 00:39:44,446
- No. Listen to me.
- Tell me something.

387
00:39:46,083 --> 00:39:48,984
lf your company acquires that
contract, what'll be your share?

388
00:39:49,153 --> 00:39:50,984
- That's not the problem.
- Then?

389
00:39:51,155 --> 00:39:52,986
- lt's something else.
- Then, let's solve the problem!

390
00:39:53,157 --> 00:39:54,988
Mr. Suri, how was the game?

391
00:39:55,159 --> 00:39:59,994
Please don't joke. Doing business
and drinking whisky is my forte.

392
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:02,496
Else, even l would be preparing
for Wimbledon like my son!

393
00:40:04,668 --> 00:40:09,002
DK, the joy of
watching your son grow!

394
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:12,200
lt wasn't the same
even in my youth!

395
00:40:14,845 --> 00:40:17,040
A son is important.

396
00:40:17,214 --> 00:40:20,547
Your son must be handling
your business now, right?

397
00:40:20,751 --> 00:40:22,048
l'll leave now.

398
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:25,086
Hey, you wanted to discuss
a problem. What is it?

399
00:40:27,191 --> 00:40:29,091
-What's it?
-We'll talk later.

400
00:40:48,746 --> 00:40:50,646
Yes, l will inform him.

401
00:41:05,162 --> 00:41:07,562
Mr. Bansal, this is
a foundation problem.

402
00:41:07,731 --> 00:41:10,063
As per Mr. Malhotra's
original estimates...

403
00:41:10,234 --> 00:41:13,067
...you'll find mica content
at a depth of 40 feet.

404
00:41:13,237 --> 00:41:14,568
But as perthe...

405
00:41:15,706 --> 00:41:18,106
Sorry, sir.
l have to go home.

406
00:41:41,265 --> 00:41:43,165
- lndu, where are you going?
-Anywhere! ...l don't know!

407
00:41:43,334 --> 00:41:45,165
Please listen to me!

408
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:46,667
l don't want to listen!

409
00:41:47,271 --> 00:41:49,671
Please listen to me for a minute!

410
00:41:55,312 --> 00:41:57,212
l didn't know that the boy
was going to come here.

411
00:41:57,381 --> 00:42:00,214
- Stop lying!
- l swear, l didn't know!

412
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:03,081
Come what may, that boy is
not going to come to this house!

413
00:42:03,287 --> 00:42:06,120
- Do you need the taxi or not?
-We don't want it!

414
00:42:11,228 --> 00:42:12,627
Take this.

415
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:17,129
lndu, listen!
Just for a few days!

416
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:19,633
Please, lndu! What can l
do now if he's coming here?

417
00:42:19,803 --> 00:42:21,634
Do what you want, but he
is not going to come here!

418
00:42:21,805 --> 00:42:25,673
l promise he won't stay here
for more than 2-3 days.

419
00:42:25,843 --> 00:42:27,174
l promise.

420
00:42:27,344 --> 00:42:29,403
l do not trust you anymore!

421
00:42:31,782 --> 00:42:36,219
You'd said, my problem is yours
too. Won't you help me this time?

422
00:42:36,820 --> 00:42:40,221
Mummy, ask sisterto return
my scented rubber!

423
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:43,326
Quiet! lt was my rubber!
So what if l took it?!

424
00:42:43,527 --> 00:42:46,724
What do you want?! That you
do any wrong and l endure it?!

425
00:42:46,897 --> 00:42:50,731
l'm also human, l have feelings.
Have you everthought about that?

426
00:42:51,335 --> 00:42:54,236
And these children...
what will you tell them?!

427
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:56,430
l'll beat you! ...
Mummy, just look at her!

428
00:42:56,640 --> 00:43:00,235
Mummy, two of my sums were
wrong!

429
00:43:00,377 --> 00:43:03,540
Come on, l'll show you.

430
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:06,648
Come on, mummy!

431
00:43:08,886 --> 00:43:11,548
Papa, please carry me.

432
00:43:16,493 --> 00:43:19,189
Now take me inside.

433
00:43:26,303 --> 00:43:28,203
Mini and Winky, please come here.

434
00:43:29,306 --> 00:43:30,739
What's it?

435
00:43:31,342 --> 00:43:34,243
A boy will be coming
to stay in our house.

436
00:43:34,411 --> 00:43:36,538
-Who is he?
- His name is...

437
00:43:40,384 --> 00:43:44,787
His mummy is dead,
so he's coming to stay with us.

438
00:43:44,955 --> 00:43:46,786
But who was his mummy?

439
00:43:48,892 --> 00:43:52,293
She was our distant relative.

440
00:43:52,463 --> 00:43:54,693
Mummy, how old is he?

441
00:43:55,399 --> 00:43:56,798
He...

442
00:44:02,272 --> 00:44:04,206
He is 8-9 years old.

443
00:44:04,808 --> 00:44:09,677
Such a small boy! My exams are
nearing, he won't let me study!

444
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:11,711
No. He'll play with me.

445
00:44:11,915 --> 00:44:15,214
Where is his father?
Why doesn't he go to him?

446
00:44:16,353 --> 00:44:19,254
His father has gone away.

447
00:44:19,857 --> 00:44:21,256
Leaving him behind?

448
00:44:24,561 --> 00:44:26,756
My papa would have
never done that!

449
00:44:26,930 --> 00:44:29,763
Children, go to
your room and sleep.

450
00:44:37,007 --> 00:44:39,305
- Come on, hurry.
- lt will be great fun now!

451
00:44:39,476 --> 00:44:40,807
lt will be no fun!

452
00:44:43,414 --> 00:44:44,813
You took care.

453
00:44:45,416 --> 00:44:48,351
l was taking care of my children!

454
00:45:29,426 --> 00:45:31,121
Shall l roll the window down?

455
00:46:04,394 --> 00:46:06,294
Look, that's the Old Fort.

456
00:46:07,397 --> 00:46:12,096
lt's a... very old... fort!

457
00:46:13,403 --> 00:46:16,702
lt was built by Sher Shah Suri
...or perhaps Humayun...

458
00:46:16,907 --> 00:46:20,809
There's a big zoo inside now.
There are many animals and a...

459
00:46:21,011 --> 00:46:22,842
Did you know my mummy?

460
00:46:25,449 --> 00:46:27,349
Y... y... yes. Yes, l did know her.

461
00:46:27,551 --> 00:46:28,950
And papa?

462
00:46:30,487 --> 00:46:33,183
Not papa.

463
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:40,896
Mummy used to say that
l'll surely find my papa.

464
00:46:41,498 --> 00:46:46,401
Even mummy is no more. lf papa
does come, how will he find me?

465
00:46:47,504 --> 00:46:51,406
He will, son... he will find you.

466
00:47:02,452 --> 00:47:04,852
Mini, he is Rahul.

467
00:47:08,058 --> 00:47:09,855
Winky dear, come here.

468
00:47:11,128 --> 00:47:13,858
Rahul, she is Winky.

469
00:47:16,466 --> 00:47:19,367
She is my mummy...
Mummy, he is Rahul.

470
00:47:25,776 --> 00:47:28,870
Will Rahul sleep in my room?

471
00:47:29,079 --> 00:47:31,013
No. His bed has been
put in the study.

472
00:47:31,515 --> 00:47:33,915
But l study there.

473
00:47:34,117 --> 00:47:37,450
My dear, it's a matter
of only a few days.

474
00:47:38,555 --> 00:47:41,456
Abdul, keep his baggage
in the study.

475
00:47:48,565 --> 00:47:50,965
Both of you come upstairs.

476
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:13,378
Get up, this is my place.
l sit with papa.

477
00:48:17,527 --> 00:48:18,926
Go and sit there.

478
00:48:33,076 --> 00:48:36,443
Abdul... has not brought the rice.

479
00:49:02,005 --> 00:49:04,872
l had a puppy
whose name was also Mini.

480
00:49:05,042 --> 00:49:06,441
Eat quietly, Mini.

481
00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:08,578
When papa used to call
the puppy, l'd come running.

482
00:49:08,946 --> 00:49:11,915
And when he'd call me,
the puppy would come running.

483
00:49:13,984 --> 00:49:16,248
Mummy is upset today.

484
00:49:31,601 --> 00:49:33,501
lndu, aren't you going to eat?

485
00:54:26,963 --> 00:54:28,055
Son.

486
00:54:34,971 --> 00:54:36,871
What are you
doing all alone here?

487
00:54:37,073 --> 00:54:38,904
Gazing at the stars.

488
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:44,378
Mummy used to say that
if you see a shooting star...

489
00:54:44,581 --> 00:54:46,913
...your wish gets fulfilled.

490
00:54:50,553 --> 00:54:52,453
Look, uncle, a shooting star!

491
00:54:53,056 --> 00:54:55,115
-Where is it?
- lt's disappeared.

492
00:54:55,859 --> 00:54:57,952
- Did you wish for something?
-Yes.

493
00:54:58,261 --> 00:55:00,320
-What?
- l can't tell you.

494
00:55:01,431 --> 00:55:02,329
Why?

495
00:55:07,537 --> 00:55:10,335
l see... Should we go inside?

496
00:55:16,980 --> 00:55:17,878
Yes?

497
00:55:18,181 --> 00:55:20,479
Shall l tell you
what l wished for?

498
00:55:24,020 --> 00:55:27,922
l prayed that l'd find my papa.

499
00:55:35,632 --> 00:55:37,725
Come on, papa, it's getting late.

500
00:55:38,034 --> 00:55:40,935
Papa, come on.
lt's getting very late.

501
00:55:41,104 --> 00:55:42,503
He's taking so long.

502
00:55:53,616 --> 00:55:55,516
The children are getting late.

503
00:56:11,501 --> 00:56:13,401
Did you know my mummy?

504
00:56:16,005 --> 00:56:17,404
No!

505
00:56:22,045 --> 00:56:23,740
But uncle knew her.

506
00:56:24,547 --> 00:56:25,946
l know!

507
00:56:45,101 --> 00:56:47,001
What is it? Why are you
looking at me that way?

508
00:56:47,604 --> 00:56:51,506
Even my mummy used to wear
a similarfloral print sari.

509
00:56:53,143 --> 00:56:56,044
Fine... Let me work now.

510
00:57:06,556 --> 00:57:08,956
And how have you let
that boy stay in your house?!

511
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:14,461
l haven't. He just came home.

512
00:57:16,065 --> 00:57:17,965
What could l do?

513
00:57:19,068 --> 00:57:24,768
Whenever l see him,
l think of DK and that girl.

514
00:57:26,109 --> 00:57:30,478
Chanda, it seems as if
all relationships are a farce.

515
00:57:32,615 --> 00:57:34,014
lt seems as if...

516
00:57:36,152 --> 00:57:39,451
...such incidents occur
only in other people's lives.

517
00:57:45,161 --> 00:57:47,459
l don't know what to do now.

518
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:15,022
lndu, the weakeryou become,
the more you will have to endure.

519
00:58:19,128 --> 00:58:20,823
Yes, l'll be there.

520
00:58:22,131 --> 00:58:23,530
l'll be back in a jiffy.

521
00:58:42,218 --> 00:58:47,121
When the Major left me,
even l'd felt defeated like you.

522
00:58:47,290 --> 00:58:49,622
But look at me now.
What do l lack?

523
00:58:49,792 --> 00:58:54,627
l work, l live for myself,
...the way l want to!

524
00:58:55,231 --> 00:58:57,131
